4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, a county board of registrars
6 is required to purge an elector when the elector has
7 become disqualified to vote.
8 Under existing law, a county board of registrars
9 is required to change an elector's status to inactive
10 if the elector has not voted in four years.
11 Under existing law, if a county board of
12 registrars determines that an elector has moved to a
13 different address, sends a notice to the elector, and
14 the elector fails to respond to the notice, the board
15 is required to change the elector's status to inactive.
16 This bill would prohibit a county board of
17 registrars from purging, making inactive, or otherwise
18 removing an elector from the statewide voter
19 registration list within the 90-day period before any
20 regular election.
21 This bill would also make nonsubstantive,
22 technical revisions to update the existing code
23 language to current style.
24
