116 "§17-4-9
117 (a) Any voter who fails to vote for four years in his
118 or her county shall have his or her name placed on an inactive
119 voter list by the localcounty board of registrars. Once on the
120 inactive list, the voter shall reidentify with the localcounty
121 board of registrars in order to again have his or her name
122 placed on the active voter registration list. Notwithstanding
123 the foregoing, if a voter on the inactive list goes to his or
124 her polling place to vote on an election day and identifies
125 himself or herself to the election official responsible for
126 the voter registration list update, suchthe voter shall be
127 permitted to vote provided the voter completes a voter
128 reidentification form.
129 (b) The county board of registrars may not place any
130 voter on the inactive voter list, or otherwise remove a voter
131 from the active voter registration list, within 90 days of any
132 election held in the state, pursuant to Section 2 of this
133 act."
134 "§17-4-30
135 (a) Beginning in February 2025, and in February of
