218 "§17-4-39
219 (a)(1) The board of registrars shall be responsible for
220 entering and updating in a timely manner the names and
221 information of the electors who register to vote and vote in
222 each election into the state voter registration list and for
223 conducting regular voter list maintenance activities as
224 directed by the Secretary of State and otherwise provided by
Page 8

directed by the Secretary of State and otherwise provided by
HB628 INTRODUCED
225 law, including processing registered individuals identified by
226 programs conducted pursuant to subsection (b). Removal of any
227 registered individual determined to be improperly registered
228 may be accomplished at any time by a majority vote of the
229 board.
230 (2) Notwithstanding subdivision (1), a board of
231 registrars may not remove an individual from the state voter
232 registration list in the 90-day period before any regular
233 election is held in the state, pursuant to Section 2 of this
234 act.
235 (b)(1) The Secretary of State shall be responsible for
236 directly conducting regular state voter registration list
237 maintenance programs to ensure database integrity. These
238 programs shall be known as the Alabama Voter Integrity
239 Database (AVID). The Alabama Voter Integrity Database shall
240 compare the state voter registration list to:
241 a. Alabama State Law Enforcement Agency driver license
242 and nondriver identification card data to identify registered
243 voters in Alabama who have moved and obtained a driver license
244 or nondriver identification card in another state or who have
245 registered to vote in Alabama and then applied for a foreign
246 national driver license or nondriver identification card;
247 b. State-to-state voter list data to identify
248 individuals who are registered to vote in Alabama but who are
249 also registered to vote in another state, including
250 individuals who may have voted in the same or a similar
251 election in both states, with priority given to data from
252 states in close geographical proximity to Alabama;
Page 9

states in close geographical proximity to Alabama;
HB628 INTRODUCED
253 c. The National Change of Address database to identify
254 individuals who are registered to vote in Alabama but have
255 notified the United States Postal Service that they have
256 relocated to a new county within the state or an address
257 outside of Alabama;
258 d. Social Security Death Index data to identify
259 deceased individuals who are registered to vote and may have
260 died out of state; and
261 e. United States Department of Homeland Security
262 Citizenship and Immigration Services data to identify
263 individuals who are registered to vote in Alabama but are
264 ineligible to vote because they are noncitizens.
265 (2) Individuals identified shall be timely communicated
266 by the Secretary of State to the appropriate board or boards
267 of registrars to process.
268 (c) Not later than February 1, annually, the Secretary
269 of State shall collect and publish data from each county
270 specifying the number of voters who were removed from the
271 voter registration list during the previous calendar year."
272 Section 2. (a) The board of registrars for each county,
273 or the Secretary of State if acting as the board's agent, may
274 not purge, make inactive, or otherwise remove any elector from
275 the computerized statewide voter registration list within the
276 90-day period before any regular election that occurs in the
277 state.
278 (b) For purposes of this section, "regular election"
279 means any regularly scheduled and held municipal, county, or
280 statewide election. Regarding statewide elections, the term
Page 10

statewide election. Regarding statewide elections, the term
HB628 INTRODUCED
281 includes primary, primary runoff, and general elections.
282 Section 3. This act shall become effective on July 1,
283 2026.
